The paper discusses the vulnerability of machine learning models to membership inference attacks, which is a security and privacy concern. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also involves the use of machine learning techniques to perform the attack, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper evaluates the factors that influence the leakage and proposes mitigation strategies, which could fall under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
